The paper deals with problems related to geometric graphs and optimization, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of finding minimum spanning trees is a classic problem in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), and the paper provides new approximation algorithms and inapproximability results for this problem. The paper also involves combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT) in the context of degree-bounded spanning trees. Finally, the paper discusses the worst-case performance of the algorithms, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
